caption: This Pizza... A Native New Yorker.. Born & Raised Hybrid BK/Queens/with a kiss of LI .. there is NOTHING like it. I refuse to leave without a slice or ummm a pie💖 We as New Yorkers have it sooo good.. no idea. Bless up “Not Ray’s Pizza.” #RockNRoll Charlie 🦋

Normally, Not Rays is amazing. However tonight, I am at a loss for words. I ordered their signature meat slice, which is essentially two slices layered together with meat on top and in the middle. I used to buy from Not Rays for years, after a while, the cheese and sauce changed drastically, I guess they were trying to save money by ordering cheap supplies, after numerous complaints, they put the right cheese/sauce on pizzas. After the pandemic, the bread has changed drastically. I cant digest the bread or will throw it up later or dont eat all the pizza at all. they are doing something with the bread. I bragged about this pizzeria for years but I am embarrassed to suggest it to anyone due to the fact that they are using something cheap to make the bread which makes the pizza suck because you dont want to finish it. I will go somewhere else until they change. quality over quantity.

Really want to give this place 5 stars. The pizza is delicious. The first time I ordered from here, I asked for Chicago Style--cut in squares--and it wasn't a issue. I received the pizza the way I ordered and all was good. Then there was the second time ordered, and now the third, tonight. Asked for pizza same way. Didn't get it the way I asked either time. I excused it the second time because anyone can make mistakes. But now this time it came not the way I ordered, and I said it very clear and the guy on the phone repeated it back to me, so he knew what I was asking for. So now I have to give 3 stars. And potentially not order again, for the simple fact that it should matter what your customer orders and how they order it as the customer is paying--and the pizza is not exactly cheap. Not a happy customer.
